org.archive.wayback.exception

Class AccessControlException

  • java.lang.Object
    • java.lang.Throwable
      • java.lang.Exception
        • org.archive.wayback.exception.WaybackException
          • org.archive.wayback.exception.AccessControlException
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Serializable
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    AdministrativeAccessControlException, RobotAccessControlException, RobotNotAvailableException, RobotTimedOutAccessControlException

    public class AccessControlException
extends WaybackException
    Exception indicating no captures can be replayed because entire URL is blocked by robots.txt or other type of exclusion rules.

    This exception will not be thrown for individual captures. Per-capture exclusion will just make such captures invisible, and no exception will be throwsn (unless there's no captures at all as a result, in which case ResourceNotInArchiveException will be thrown).

    Author:
    brad
